SCENE STRUCTURE GUIDANCE
=========================
An object is used to amplify a physical threat — its presence in the dialogue is key:
  1. Argument — a dispute escalates in a space where the object is accessible.
  2. Grab / display — perpetrator picks up or references the object; victim notices.
  3. Threat — perpetrator's language makes the object's function as a threat explicit.
  4. Victim reaction — escalating fear; attempts to leave, talk perpetrator down, or comply.
  5. Standoff — scene ends at peak tension; no resolution within this clip.
The object itself will not make a sound in the spoken layer — only references to it.

